      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The Supreme Court has powerfully used substantive due process to secure rights, most notably in *Griswold v. Connecticut*, which established a constitutional right to marital privacy. Furthermore, the protection of personal autonomy was cemented in *Roe v. Wade*, recognizing a fundamental right to bodily integrity. These decisions demonstrate how the Court has acted as a necessary bulwark against government intrusion into private life. These rulings prove that the amendment is a dynamic tool for protecting individual freedom.",
      "source": "target",
